ADRIAN This is Helmsley.
We hear a muffled, raspy voice through the speakers.
Harry Helmsley stands beside the cruise ship's Captain.
VOICE No, this is Helmsley.
ADRIAN Dad!...
ADRIAN Is that you?
Adrian is ecstatic.
Captain Michaels explains.
CAPTAIN MICHAELS We should have a visual of the `Freedom of the Seas' shortly.
ADRIAN Dad.
ADRIAN We're coming to pick you guys up.
ADRIAN How's Tony?
Harry looks over at Tony who's listening, smiling.
HARRY HELMSLEY He's fine, son.
HARRY HELMSLEY We're all fine.
ADRIAN See you guys soon.
ADRIAN Bye dad.
Harry hangs up.
He picks up Tony, embracing him wildly.
Adrian, still excited from speaking with his dad, grabs Laura and kisses her on the lips.
She squeals.
ANHEUSER Put that woman down Helmsley.
Adrian looks at Anheuser, unsure of what he might say.
ANHEUSER (CONT'D) Young guys like you with your idealistic dreams, you think you can change the world...
Adrian and Laura exchange a look.
ANHEUSER (CONT'D) I just pray to God, that you keep on making the right calls...
ANHEUSER (CONT'D) in this new world of ours.
Adrian nods and with a smile to Laura turns to leave.
ANHEUSER (CONT'D) Mr. Helmsley, one more thing.
Adrian turns back.
ANHEUSER (CONT'D) There was no one.
ADRIAN Pardon me?
ANHEUSER There was no white kid better than you.
ANHEUSER I'm terribly sorry I said that.
Anheuser puts out his hand.
Adrian takes it.
CAPTAIN MICHAELS This is your Captain speaking.
CAPTAIN MICHAELS Standby to open Deck 1.
OFFICER Standing by Sir.
Neng pushes his brother Lin in a wheelchair onto the deck next to his parents.
Mrs. Pang turns to her husband.
MRS. PANG I wonder will the clouds look the same and the stars?
MR.PANG Do not fear.
MR.PANG Some things will never change.
The old Chinese man forces a little smile.
Closer to the front of this crowd Jackson approaches Noah.
JACKSON I thought you might want this.
He takes Noah's cell phone from his pocket and hands it to him.
NOAH Do you think I'll still get a signal ...
NOAH Dad?
Jackson is touched to hear him use that word.
He smiles and hugs him.
Adrian, Laura and Anheuser arrive alongside them.
ADRIAN I finally finished your book Jackson.
KATE Really?
KATE You may well be the first person who ever got to the end.
Jackson looks at her, smiling playfully.
JACKSON Excuse me, I believe he's addressing the author.
JACKSON Well, what did you think?
Adrian smiles.
ADRIAN I'd say...
ADRIAN those astronauts of yours would be shitting themselves, if they knew all their relatives are now stuck in the South Pole.
Suddenly a horn sounds and the sealed deck doors let off a burst of pressurised air.
A murmur goes through the crowd.
Everyone is silent as the huge deck doors slowly begin to roll back and light streams in.
The Pang family try to see over people's heads, even Anheuser looks hopeful.
Jackson pulls his family close as the first rays of daylight hit their faces.
Hatches unseal all around the ship.
Sun streams through the clouds.
Everywhere people emerge outside, into the light of day.
A majestic moment.
They all stare in awe at the waters receding against the ice- covered mountain peaks.
Caesar lets out a YELP of joy.
Almost as soon as the doors have opened, the ship's HELICOPTERS take off, flying towards a stunning site--
The `Freedom of the Seas' is perched on a mountain peak, surrounded by calm waters.
Behind it, they see the most beautiful rainbow.
This is the new world.
And again we hear Mozart's Adagio...
